28/07/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Chief of General Staff Hilmi Ozkok and his Greek counterpart, Admiral Panayiotis Hinofotis, discussed the implementation of confidence-building measures between their two countries on Thursday (27 July), the second day of Hinofotis's trip to Ankara. The officials talked about overcoming bilateral tensions stemming from incidents involving Turkish and Greek patrol jets over the Aegean Sea. This is the first visit of a Greek armed forces chief to Turkey since 1974. (Kathimerini - 28/07/06)
